//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_cygwin}

NOTE: Establishes privileged BURN trust against a Cygwin node by writing
the privileged {burn_regime} profile and driving the Cygwin-specific
{busn_garrison} ceremony.
Idempotent on re-run.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
The remote Windows account named in {burn_user} is a member of the
local Administrators group on the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
OpenSSH server is reachable on {burn_host} from the calling station,
and the operator can complete the console-side handshake at the
Windows keyboard (or RDP).

//axhos_step
. *Write profile*: persist the privileged {burn_regime} profile to the
station subtree with `{burn_tier} = privileged`

//axhos_step
. *Console handshake*: drive the Cygwin-specific console ceremony to
install the station pubkey into
`C:\ProgramData\ssh\administrators_authorized_keys`

//axhos_step
. *Probe trust*: confirm passwordless SSH to the privileged account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
The privileged {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally and the
station's {burn_ssh_pubkey} is trusted on the remote Cygwin node.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the trust handshake completes and the verification probe
succeeds.
Non-zero on profile-write failure, console-handshake refusal, or final
SSH probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_wsl}

NOTE: Establishes privileged BURN trust against a WSL node by writing
the privileged {burn_regime} profile and driving the WSL-specific
{busn_garrison} ceremony.
Idempotent on re-run.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
The remote Windows account hosting the WSL distribution is a member of
the local Administrators group, and the WSL distribution named in
{burn_command} is registered for that account on the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
OpenSSH server is reachable on {burn_host} from the calling station,
and the operator can complete the console-side handshake at the
Windows keyboard (or RDP).

//axhos_step
. *Write profile*: persist the privileged {burn_regime} profile to the
station subtree with `{burn_tier} = privileged` and the WSL launcher
recorded in {burn_command}

//axhos_step
. *Console handshake*: drive the WSL-specific console ceremony — bash
owns control flow and PowerShell is the syscall layer — to install the
station pubkey into
`C:\ProgramData\ssh\administrators_authorized_keys`

//axhos_step
. *Probe trust*: confirm passwordless SSH to the privileged account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
The privileged {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally and the
station's {burn_ssh_pubkey} is trusted on the remote WSL node.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the trust handshake completes and the verification probe
succeeds.
Non-zero on profile-write failure, WSL launcher unavailability,
console-handshake refusal, or final SSH probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_garrison_powershell}

NOTE: Establishes privileged BURN trust against a Windows node using
PowerShell as the remote shell, by writing the privileged
{burn_regime} profile and driving the PowerShell-specific
{busn_garrison} ceremony.
Idempotent on re-run.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
The remote Windows account named in {burn_user} is a member of the
local Administrators group on the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
OpenSSH server is reachable on {burn_host} from the calling station,
the OpenSSH default shell is set (or settable) to `powershell.exe`,
and the operator can complete the console-side handshake at the
Windows keyboard (or RDP).

//axhos_step
. *Write profile*: persist the privileged {burn_regime} profile to the
station subtree with `{burn_tier} = privileged` and {burn_command}
naming the PowerShell launcher

//axhos_step
. *Console handshake*: drive the PowerShell-specific console ceremony
to install the station pubkey into
`C:\ProgramData\ssh\administrators_authorized_keys`

//axhos_step
. *Probe trust*: confirm passwordless SSH to the privileged account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
The privileged {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally and the
station's {burn_ssh_pubkey} is trusted on the remote Windows node
under the PowerShell shell choice.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the trust handshake completes and the verification probe
succeeds.
Non-zero on profile-write failure, console-handshake refusal, or final
SSH probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_conscript_cygwin}

NOTE: Creates an ephemeral workload OS user on a Windows node with a
Cygwin shell, and provisions a corresponding workload {burn_regime}
profile locally.
Uses a named privileged BURN as authority for the remote-user creation.
The Cygwin shell choice is independent of the privileged BURN's shell.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A privileged-tier {burn_regime} profile exists locally and is
{bust_knock}-responsive against the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
The privileged account on the target node carries authority sufficient
to create local OS users and assign Cygwin login defaults.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate via privileged BURN*: open an authenticated session to
the target node using the privileged profile

//axhos_step
. *Create workload user*: provision a fresh OS user with a Cygwin shell
default; capture the temporary credential or pubkey trust as defined
by the platform ceremony

//axhos_step
. *Write workload profile*: persist a workload {burn_regime} profile
locally with `{burn_tier} = workload` and a reference to the privileged
authority used to create the user

//axhos_step
. *Probe new account*: confirm passwordless SSH to the workload account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
A new workload OS user exists on the remote node, a corresponding
workload {burn_regime} profile is persisted locally, and the new
account is reachable over passwordless SSH.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when remote-user creation, local profile write, and verification
probe all succeed.
Non-zero when the privileged BURN refuses, remote-user creation fails,
the local profile cannot be written, or the final probe fails.

//axhob_operation
{bust_conscript_wsl}

NOTE: Creates an ephemeral workload OS user on a Windows node with a
WSL shell, and provisions a corresponding workload {burn_regime}
profile locally.
Uses a named privileged BURN as authority for the remote-user
creation.
The WSL shell choice is independent of the privileged BURN's shell.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A privileged-tier {burn_regime} profile exists locally and is
{bust_knock}-responsive against the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
A WSL distribution is registered (or registrable) for the new workload
account on the target node.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate via privileged BURN*: open an authenticated session to
the target node using the privileged profile

//axhos_step
. *Create workload user*: provision a fresh OS user, register the WSL
distribution under that user, and capture the temporary credential or
pubkey trust as defined by the platform ceremony

//axhos_step
. *Write workload profile*: persist a workload {burn_regime} profile
locally with `{burn_tier} = workload`, {burn_command} naming the WSL
launcher, and a reference to the privileged authority used

//axhos_step
. *Probe new account*: confirm passwordless SSH to the workload account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
A new workload OS user exists on the remote node with a registered WSL
distribution, a corresponding workload {burn_regime} profile is
persisted locally, and the new account is reachable over passwordless
SSH.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when remote-user creation, WSL registration, local profile write,
and verification probe all succeed.
Non-zero on any of: privileged-BURN refusal, remote-user creation
failure, WSL registration failure, local profile write failure, or
final probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_conscript_powershell}

NOTE: Creates an ephemeral workload OS user on a Windows node with a
PowerShell shell, and provisions a corresponding workload
{burn_regime} profile locally.
Uses a named privileged BURN as authority for the remote-user
creation.
The PowerShell shell choice is independent of the privileged BURN's
shell.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A privileged-tier {burn_regime} profile exists locally and is
{bust_knock}-responsive against the target node.

//axhoq_precondition
The OpenSSH default shell on the target node is set to (or settable
to) `powershell.exe` for the workload account.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate via privileged BURN*: open an authenticated session to
the target node using the privileged profile

//axhos_step
. *Create workload user*: provision a fresh OS user with PowerShell as
the login shell, and capture the temporary credential or pubkey trust
as defined by the platform ceremony

//axhos_step
. *Write workload profile*: persist a workload {burn_regime} profile
locally with `{burn_tier} = workload`, {burn_command} naming the
PowerShell launcher, and a reference to the privileged authority used

//axhos_step
. *Probe new account*: confirm passwordless SSH to the workload account
succeeds via {bust_knock}

//axhog_guarantee
A new workload OS user exists on the remote node with PowerShell as the
login shell, a corresponding workload {burn_regime} profile is
persisted locally, and the new account is reachable over passwordless
SSH.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when remote-user creation, local profile write, and verification
probe all succeed.
Non-zero on any of: privileged-BURN refusal, remote-user creation
failure, shell-association failure, local profile write failure, or
final probe failure.

//axhob_operation
{bust_discharge}

NOTE: Removes a workload user from a node and deletes the local
workload {burn_regime} profile.
The workload profile encodes its privileged authority; {bust_discharge}
uses that authority to delete the remote OS user, then unlinks the
local profile file.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burn_regime} profile with `{burn_tier} = workload` exists at the
given {burn_alias} and references a privileged authority that is
currently {bust_knock}-responsive.

//axhos_step
. *Resolve authority*: read the workload profile and resolve its
referenced privileged authority

//axhos_step
. *Delete remote user*: authenticate via the privileged authority and
delete the remote OS user named by the workload profile

//axhos_step
. *Remove local profile*: unlink the local workload profile file and
its associated key material under the station subtree

//axhog_guarantee
The workload OS user no longer exists on the remote node, and the local
workload profile file is removed.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 on full removal.
Non-zero when the privileged authority refuses, the remote-user
deletion fails, or the local profile cannot be removed.

//axhob_operation
{bust_inventory}

NOTE: Reports workload users currently provisioned on a node.
Scope is the node's full workload-user population — not just the
calling station's history.
Queries the node via the named privileged BURN.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burn_alias}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burn_regime} profile with `{burn_tier} = privileged` exists at the
given {burn_alias} and authenticates without prompting.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate via privileged BURN*: open an authenticated session to
the target node using the privileged profile

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate workload users*: list OS users whose names match the
workload-user naming convention defined by the platform ceremony

//axhos_step
. *Display roster*: print the discovered identities together with any
shell or last-login metadata exposed by the platform

//axhog_guarantee
No remote OS state was modified and no local profile was written.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 on successful enumeration; a zero-user roster is success.
Non-zero when the privileged BURN refuses, the node cannot be queried,
or the user-listing call returns a non-success status.

